sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / Dashboard
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Reconciler as KServeInferencePayload<br/>Reconciler
    participant Storage as Storage Backend<br/>(PVC/DB/MinIO)
    participant ModelMesh as ModelMesh<br/>Serving Runtime
    participant KServeIS as KServe<br/>InferenceService
    participant ModelServer as KServe/ModelMesh<br/>Model Server
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>OpenShift Monitoring
    participant MariaDB as MariaDB/MySQL<br/>3306/TCP JDBC

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 1: Inference Payload Ingestion (ModelMesh -> TrustyAI)
    ModelMesh->>TrustyAI: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>8080/TCP HTTP, No Auth
    TrustyAI->>Reconciler: InferencePartialPayload<br/>(request + response matching)
    Reconciler->>Storage: Persist complete observation
    Note right of Storage: PVC: filesystem /inputs<br/>DB: JDBC 3306/TCP<br/>MinIO: S3 HTTP API

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 2: CloudEvents Payload Ingestion (KServe -> TrustyAI)
    KServeIS->>TrustyAI: CloudEvent (Knative Funqy)<br/>org.kubeflow.serving.inference.*<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    TrustyAI->>Reconciler: CloudEvent payload
    Reconciler->>Storage: Persist observation

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 3: Fairness/Drift Metric Computation
    Client->>Route: POST /metrics/group/fairness/spd<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    Route->>TrustyAI: Forward request<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Read observation data
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: DataFrame
    TrustyAI-->>Route: Metric result (JSON)
    Route-->>Client: HTTP 200 Response

    Note over TrustyAI,Prometheus: Scheduled Metric Publishing (every 5s)
    loop PrometheusScheduler @Scheduled(5s)
        TrustyAI->>Storage: Read observation data
        Storage-->>TrustyAI: DataFrame
        TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Compute SPD, DIR, drift metrics
        TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Publish to Micrometer gauges<br/>(trustyai_spd, trustyai_dir)
    end
    Prometheus->>TrustyAI: GET /q/metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
    TrustyAI-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 4: Explainability Request (ODH only - disabled in RHOAI)
    Client->>Route: POST /explainers/local/lime<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    Route->>TrustyAI: Forward request
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Read observation data
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: DataFrame
    TrustyAI->>ModelServer: HTTP inference request<br/>8080/TCP HTTP, No TLS
    ModelServer-->>TrustyAI: Prediction response
    alt gRPC path
        TrustyAI->>ModelServer: gRPC v2 inference<br/>plaintext, No Auth
        ModelServer-->>TrustyAI: gRPC response
    end
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Compute LIME explanation
    TrustyAI-->>Route: Explanation result (JSON)
    Route-->>Client: HTTP 200 Response

    Note over Client,Prometheus: Flow 5: Data Upload
    Client->>Route: POST /data/upload<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    Route->>TrustyAI: Batch model data / ground truths
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Persist uploaded data
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Confirmation
    TrustyAI-->>Route: HTTP 200
    Route-->>Client: Upload confirmed
